{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d22c214b-0c4f-48de-84e5-79e6daf397a2","content":"Update these three files:\n\n**1. `*.csproj`** — change the target framework:\n```xml\n<TargetFramework>net11.0</TargetFramework>\n```\n\n**2. `global.json`** — pin the new SDK:\n```json\n{ \"sdk\": { \"version\": \"11.0.100\" } }\n```\n\n**3. `Dockerfile`** — update base images:\n```dockerfile\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/aspnet:11.0 AS base\nFROM mcr.microsoft.com/dotnet/sdk:11.0 AS build\n```\n\nAfter updating, run `dotnet restore && dotnet build` to verify everything compiles. Also update any NuGet packages (e.g. `Microsoft.AspNetCore.*`, `Microsoft.Extensions.*`) to their 11.x versions.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c32934d8-395d-488c-893d-919100ea6123","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking how to update their .NET project from .NET 10 to .NET 11. This is a straightforward guidance question — no code to explore. I'll provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":262},"id":"73289aee-8095-47aa-b64e-5749290f6b0b","timestamp":"2026-04-03T00:59:07.886Z","parentId":"edcd4acf-dd05-4bfd-9a43-2df4930a062f"}
